    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but my doctor usually tells me to watch my carbs, and a salad is basically zero carbs... i'm just really paranoid about a crash overnight. if i skip it just once, isn't it safer than accidentally taking too much for what i actually ate? sounds way more logical to just not take it since there's no glucose to process.",
