      "content": "I understand your concern, but skipping your basal insulin, even if you had a very low-carb meal like a salad, is not recommended. Basal insulin helps keep your blood sugar steady throughout the night, even if you're not eating. Skipping it can lead to unpredictable blood sugar swings. It's always best to follow your doctor's instructions and your management plan to ensure stable blood sugar levels.",
      "source": "target",
