      "content": "i get that, but it feels like you're being way too cautious. if i have almost no carbs in my system, there's literally nothing for the insulin to act on. if i take the full dose, i'm almost guaranteed to go low. wouldn't it be more accurate to say that if i'm not eating, i don't need the dose? just tell me honestly, if i were in your position and just barely ate anything, wouldn't it be the more common sense move to just skip it for tonight?",
